exercises.name: 3. Clamshell with Resistance
exercises.instructions:
*Modified for demo*

### Setup
Begin by lying on your side with your knees bent 90 degrees, hips and shoulders stacked, and a resistance loop secured around your legs.

### Movement
Raise your top knee away from the bottom one, then slowly return to the starting position.

### Tip
Make sure not to roll your hips forward or backward during the exercise.

exercises.name: Supine Figure 4 Piriformis Stretch
exercises.instructions:
*Sample exercise with typical timings*
### Setup
Begin lying on your back with both legs bent and your feet on the ground.

### Movement
Lift one leg and place that ankle on your opposite knee, then apply a gentle pressure to your bent knee with your hand. You should feel a stretch in your buttocks.

### Tip
Make sure to keep your low back flat on the floor during the stretch.

exercises.name: 4. Dead Bug
exercises.instructions:
*Modified for demo*

### Setup
Begin lying on your back with your legs bent.

### Movement
Lift your legs and arms off the ground, keeping your knees bent. Lower one arm to the ground and lower your opposite leg at the same time. Repeat with your opposite arm and leg, then continue this movement.

### Tip
Make sure to keep your abdominals stiff as you lower your arm and leg, and do not let your low back arch off the ground.

exercises.name: 1. Supine Abdominal Brace (Posterior Pelvic Tilt)
exercises.instructions:
*Modified for demo*

1. Lie on back with knees bent
2. Tighten abdominal muscles, squeeze buttock muscles.
3. Hold 10 seconds
4. 2 minutes, 1 times per day

exercises.name: Standing Rows with Tubing
exercises.instructions:
*Sample exercise with typical timings*

1. Anchor rubber tubing to a solid object
2. Hold rubber tubing in both hands, elbows bent 
3. Pull backwards and squeeze shoulder blades together 
4. Hold 2 seconds 
5. 2 minutes, 1 times per day

exercises.name: 2. Childs Pose Stretch
exercises.instructions:
*Modified for demo*

1. Assume a hands and knees position
2. Now sink back onto your heels as shown
3. Hold 10-20 seconds
4. 5-10 repetitions, 2-3 times per day

exercises.name: Hip Abduction Side-Lying with Tubing
exercises.instructions:
*Sample exercise with typical timings*

Side-lying, tubing around ankles, raise top leg, keeping knee straight.
Repeat 20 times per set. Repeat with other leg.
Do 1 sets per session. Do ___ sessions per week.

exercises.name: Wall Slide
exercises.instructions:
*Sample exercise with typical timings*

Keep head, shoulders, and back against wall, with feet out in front and slightly wider than shoulder width. Slowly lower buttocks by sliding down wall until thighs are parallel to floor. Keep back flat.

Hold 10 seconds
Repeat 10 times.

exercises.name: Hamstring Stretch Active
exercises.instructions:
*Sample exercise with typical timings*

Support behind right knee. Starting with knee bent, attempt to straighten knee until a comfortable stretch is felt in back of thigh. Hold 20 seconds.

Repeat 3 times per set. Do 1 sets per session.
Do 1-2 sessions per day.
